{
  "text": "In the group of sulfonamides (SAs), SQX showed 100% detection frequency, while SDZ and SMM showed detection frequency over 89%. With the properties of recalcitrance and hydrophilicity, SAs were prevalent in the surface water [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the group of fluoroquinolones (FQs), three antibiotics (NFX, CFX, OFX) still frequently showed detection frequency over 81.25%. Among FQs, CFX showed the highest concentration (283.5 ng/L) in November. The mean concentrations of antibiotics in this group followed the rank order: NFX (129.63 ng/L) > CFX (25.12 ng/L) > OFX (7.64 ng/L). In the group of β-lactams, the detection frequencies of LEX, PENG, PENV were more than 89.58%. The highest concentration was observed for PENV, reaching 404.9 ng/L. In the group of macrolides (MLs), TYL and ETM-H 2 O were detected at a low concentration level, in the range of not detedted (n.d)-6.2 ng/L and n.d-37.4 ng/L, respectively, which were notably lower than Australian urban water (0-60 ng/L) [CITATION_3] but higher than the South Yellow Sea (n.d-1.7 ng/L) [CITATION_4] . The detected frequency of TYL (47.92%) is lowest among 16 antibiotics. In the group of tetracyclines (TCs), TC and DC were 100% detected with concentrations up to 35.9 ng/L and 266.7 ng/L, respectively. In the group of others, the concentrations of the antibiotics were relatively low compared with the other five groups of antibiotics. LIN has been reported in ranges from 4-171 ng/L in Urban Water [CITATION_5] and 1-50 ng/L in Surface water in Spain [CITATION_6] compared to a range from n.d-11.5 ng/L in Qingcaosha Reservoir. ",
  "correct_citation": {
